'''Lamine Camara''' (born 1 January 2004) is a Senegalese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[attacking midfielder|midfielder]] for {{French football updater|Monaco}} club [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] and the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Diouloulou]], Camara played for Galaxy FA in [[Dakar]], followed by [[Casa Sports]], before joining [[Génération Foot]] in November 2019.<ref name="auto">{{cite web |url=https://footballtalentscout.net/2023/02/17/lamine-camara-one-of-the-most-gifted-senegalese-of-all-time-harold-monteiro/ |title=Lamine Camara: one of the most gifted Senegalese of all time |publisher=Football Talent Scout |date=17 February 2023 |access-date=9 November 2023 |archive-date=28 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231028073531/https://footballtalentscout.net/2023/02/17/lamine-camara-one-of-the-most-gifted-senegalese-of-all-time-harold-monteiro/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

===Metz===
In February 2023, Camara signed for French side [[FC Metz|Metz]] on a three-and-a-half-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportnewsafrica.com/breve/chan-meilleur-espoir-du-1er-tour-le-senegalais-lamine-camara-rejoint-le-fc-metz/|title=CHAN : meilleur espoir du 1er tour, le Sénégalais Lamine Camara rejoint le FC Metz|trans-title=CHAN: best hope of the 1st round, the Senegalese Lamine Camara joins FC Metz|date=1 February 2023|accessdate=24 February 2023|website=sportnewsafrica.com|language=French|archive-date=23 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230323055236/https://sportnewsafrica.com/breve/chan-meilleur-espoir-du-1er-tour-le-senegalais-lamine-camara-rejoint-le-fc-metz/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://wiwsport.com/2023/02/13/metz-lamine-camara-reagit-apres-sa-signature/|title=Metz: Lamine Camara reagit aprés sa signature|trans-title=Metz: Lamine Camara reacts after signing|date=13 February 2023|accessdate=24 February 2023|website=wiwsport.com|language=French}}</ref> On 15 April, he made his debut, coming off the bench in the 89th minute, in a 3–0 victory over [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]] in [[2022–23 Ligue 2|Ligue 2]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/640296 |title=Metz 3–0 Bordeaux |publisher=ESPN |date=15 April 2023 }}</ref> In his second match for the club, a 3–1 win at [[AS Saint-Étienne|Saint-Étienne]], Camara assisted a goal for [[Koffi Kouao]] before being sent off in the 79th minute for tripping [[Mathieu Cafaro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/ligue-2/2022-2023/asse-metz-live/539407|title=ASSE 1-3 Metz|language=French|date=22 April 2023|access-date=28 April 2025|website=L'Equipe}}</ref> After serving a suspension, Camara made two more appearances as a substitute as Metz gained promotion to [[Ligue 1]] with a third-placed finish.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/grand-est/moselle/metz/football-la-montee-en-ligue-1-pour-le-fc-metz-validee-par-la-ligue-2793610.html|title=Football: FC Metz's promotion to Ligue 1 validated by the League|date=12 June 2023|access-date=28 April 2025|website=France 3}}</ref>

Camara became a regular in the Metz team upon their return to Ligue 1 and, on 22 October, he scored his first goal for the club in a 2–1 away defeat against [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ligue1.com/articles/news/2023/10/23/camara-nets-unmissable-long-range-strike |title=Camara nets unmissable long-range strike |publisher=Ligue 1 |date=23 October 2023 }}</ref> The goal was scored from his own half, as he hit a first-time strike from a distance of {{convert|58|m|ft}} over Monaco goalkeeper [[Philipp Köhn]] after dispossessing [[Youssouf Fofana (French footballer)|Youssouf Fofana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurosport.fr/football/ligue-1/2023-2024/le-lob-de-58m-de-lamine-camara-face-a-monaco-etait-prevu-j-avais-vu-que-le-gardien-etait-loin-de-ses_sto9847768/story.shtml|title=Le lob de 58m de Lamine Camara face à Monaco était prévu : "J'avais vu que le gardien était loin de ses cages"|language=French|date=23 October 2023|access-date=28 April 2025|website=Eurosport}}</ref>

After finishing in 16th place in [[2023–24 Ligue 1|Ligue 1]], Metz faced Saint-Étienne in a two-legged play-off. Camara assisted [[Ismaël Traoré]]'s goal in the away leg and scored the opening goal in the home leg but this was not enough to stop Metz from losing 4–3 on aggregate and being relegated back to Ligue 2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/sport/article/2024/06/02/saint-etienne-remonte-en-ligue-1-metz-a-nouveau-relegue_6236951_3242.html|title=Saint-Etienne remonte en Ligue 1, Metz à nouveau relégué|language=French|date=2 June 2024|access-date=28 April 2025|website=Le Monde}}</ref>

=== Monaco ===
On 30 July 2024, Camara joined Ligue 1 club [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] for a transfer fee of €15 million, signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Transferts : Lamine Camara s'engage officiellement avec Monaco |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Lamine-camara-s-engage-officiellement-avec-monaco/1487026 |access-date=2024-08-15 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Chédeville |first=Damien |date=2024-07-30 |title=Lamine Camara is Monegasque! |url=https://www.asmonaco.com/en/lamine-camara-is-monegasque/ |access-date=2024-08-15 |website=AS Monaco |language=en-US}}</ref>

On 17 August, Camara made his debut for Monaco in a 1–0 win over Saint-Étienne at the [[Stade Louis II]] in the team's opening fixture of the [[2024–25 AS Monaco FC season|2024–25 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/ligue-1/2024-2025/monaco-asse-live/655862|title=Monaco - ASSE, le résumé du match|language=French|date=17 August 2024|access-date=28 April 2025|website=L'Equipe}}</ref> In the following match, he scored his first goal for the club in a 2–0 win over [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] and was later sent off after being shown two yellow cards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/ligue-1/lyon-monaco-0-2-les-monegasques-enfoncent-un-ol-deja-inquietant-24-08-2024-ZGEVN34HYZDCNE7LBW6Z56VQBY.php|title=Lyon-Monaco (0-2) : les Monégasques enfoncent un OL déjà inquiétant|language=French|date=24 August 2024|access-date=28 April 2025|website=Le Parisien}}</ref>

He made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut in a 2–1 win over [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] during the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|league phase]] on 19 September.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.as.com/soccer/monaco-barcelona-live-online-score-stats-and-updates-champions-league-n/|title=Monaco 2-1 Barcelona: summary, score, goals, highlights Champions League|date=19 September 2024|access-date=28 April 2025|website=AS}}</ref>

==International career==

Camara represented the Senegalese national team at the [[2022 African Nations Championship]], where he was named best young player of the group stage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.africatopsports.com/2023/01/27/chan-2022-le-senegalais-lamine-camara-nomme-meilleur-jeune-joueur-de-la-phase-de-groupes/|title=CHAN 2022: Le sénégalais Lamine Camara nommé meilleur jeune joueur de la phase de groupes|trans-title=CHAN 2022: Senegalese Lamine Camara named best young player of the group stage|first=Maïmouna|last=Sane|date=27 January 2023|accessdate=24 February 2023|website=africatopsports.com|language=French}}</ref> He went on to score the only goal of the quarter-final against [[Mauritania national football team|Mauritania]] from a penalty kick.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/663877|title=Senegal 1-0 Mauritania|date=27 January 2023|access-date=28 April 2025|website=ESPN}}</ref> In the [[2022 African Nations Championship final]], he played the full 120 minutes against host nation [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] and was one of five Senegalese players to score in the penalty shootout as Senegal won their first [[African Nations Championship]].<ref name=phenomenal>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/caf-africa-cup-of-nations/news/lamine-camaras-phenomenal-year/|title=Lamine Camara's phenomenal year|date=5 September 2023|access-date=28 April 2025|website=CAF}}</ref>

Camara was then called up to the [[Senegal national under-20 football team|Senegalese under-20 side]] for the [[2023 Africa U-20 Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fsfoot.sn/can-egypte-u2o-le-coach-malick-daf-publie-sa-liste/|title=CAN Egypte U20: Le coach Malick Daf publie sa liste|trans-title=CAN Egypt U20: Coach Malick Daf publishes his list|date=8 February 2023|accessdate=24 February 2023|website=fsfoot.sn|language=French|archive-date=20 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230220190032/https://www.fsfoot.sn/can-egypte-u2o-le-coach-malick-daf-publie-sa-liste/|url-status=dead}}</ref> He was named Player of the Tournament<ref name=phenomenal/> as Senegal were crowned champions with a perfect record, winning all six matches without conceding a goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/caf-u-20-africa-cup-of-nations/news/totalenergies-afcon-u-20-best-xi-of-the-tournament|title=TotalEnergies AFCON U-20 - Best XI of the tournament|date=5 September 2023|access-date=28 April 2025|website=CAF}}</ref>

===Senior===
In September 2023, Camara was called up to the [[Senegal national football team|senior Senegal team]] for the first time by coach [[Aliou Cissé]].<ref name=phenomenal/> He made his debut in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifier]] against [[South Sudan national football team|South Sudan]], scoring the third goal of a 4–0 win in Dakar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/news/mane-brace-helps-senegal-overpower-south-sudan-in-world-cup-qualifying/|title=Mane brace helps Senegal overpower South Sudan in World Cup qualifying|date=18 November 2023|access-date=28 April 2025|website=CAF}}</ref>

In December 2023, he was named in Senegal's squad for the postponed [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] held in the [[Ivory Coast]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/67840713|title=Afcon 2023: Senegal and Sadio Mane set for defence of title|date=29 December 2023|access-date=30 December 2023|work=BBC Sport Africa}}</ref> In the team's opening match against [[Gambia national football team|The Gambia]], he scored two goals as Senegal won 3–0.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/67908911|title=Afcon 2023: Senegal 3-0 The Gambia - Lamine Camara scores twice as holders make winning start|date=15 January 2024|access-date=28 April 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> He went on to play the full match against [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]] and the first 87 minutes of the round of 16 match, where Senegal were defeated 5–4 in a penalty shootout by host nation and eventual winners [[Côte d'Ivoire national football team|Ivory Coast]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/ckm30r3nrpgt#Line-ups|title=Senegal v Côte d'Ivoire|date=29 January 2024|access-date=28 April 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

